	<item>
		<title>2008-built rig scores multimillion-dollar drilling job offshore Canada</title>
		<link>https://www.offshore-energy.biz/2008-built-rig-scores-multimillion-dollar-drilling-job-offshore-canada/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Melisa Cavcic]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 14:57:57 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Headline]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Canada]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[hercules]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Odfjell Drilling]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[offshore drilling]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Oil and Gas]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[SFL Corporation]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.offshore-energy.biz/?p=792707</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>A semi-submersible rig, owned by SFL Corporation (SFL) and managed by Odfjell Drilling, has lined up a new drilling assignment off the coast of Canada with an undisclosed oil and gas player.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.offshore-energy.biz/2008-built-rig-scores-multimillion-dollar-drilling-job-offshore-canada/">2008-built rig scores multimillion-dollar drilling job offshore Canada</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.offshore-energy.biz">Offshore Energy</a>.</p>
]]></description>
		
		
		
		<image>https://www.offshore-energy.biz/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2024/01/Hercules-rig-Source-SFL-Corp-100x70.jpg?image-crop-positioner-ts=1706255283</image><image_medium>https://www.offshore-energy.biz/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2024/01/Hercules-rig-Source-SFL-Corp.jpg?image-crop-positioner-ts=1706255283</image_medium><is_in_depth>false</is_in_depth>	</item>
		<item>
		<title>Samsung Heavy Industries books French firm’s tank design for new LNG vessel</title>
		<link>https://www.offshore-energy.biz/samsung-heavy-industries-books-french-firms-tank-design-for-new-lng-vessel/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Melisa Cavcic]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 14:21:52 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Headline]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Gaztransport & Technigaz (GTT)]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[GTT]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[LNG]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Samsung Heavy Industries]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Samsung Heavy Industries (SHI)]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.offshore-energy.biz/?p=792729</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>French technological containment specialist Gaztransport &#38; Technigaz (GTT) has received a new tank design order for a liquefied natural gas (LNG) carrier (LNGC) from South Korea’s Samsung Heavy Industries (SHI).</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.offshore-energy.biz/samsung-heavy-industries-books-french-firms-tank-design-for-new-lng-vessel/">Samsung Heavy Industries books French firm’s tank design for new LNG vessel</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.offshore-energy.biz">Offshore Energy</a>.</p>
]]></description>
		
		
		
		<image>https://www.offshore-energy.biz/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2026/02/LNG-vessel-Source-GTT-100x70.jpg?image-crop-positioner-ts=1771505165</image><image_medium>https://www.offshore-energy.biz/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2026/02/LNG-vessel-Source-GTT.jpg?image-crop-positioner-ts=1771505165</image_medium><is_in_depth>false</is_in_depth>	</item>
		<item>
		<title>$33.4 billion acquisition of AES filling financial coffers for Panamanian firms’ $4B lawsuit</title>
		<link>https://www.offshore-energy.biz/33-4-billion-acquisition-of-aes-filling-financial-coffers-for-panamanian-firms-4b-lawsuit/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Melisa Cavcic]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 13:44:04 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Headline]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[AES]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[AES Corporation]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[blackrock]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[lawsuit]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[legal action]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[LNG]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[LNG lawsuit]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[panama]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Sinolam]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Sinolam LNG Terminal]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Sinolam Smarter Energy LNG Power]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.offshore-energy.biz/?p=792722</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Sinolam, Panamanian companies with projects in the liquefied natural gas (LNG) and power generation sector, has provided its take on the acquisition of AES Corporation by a consortium led by Global Infrastructure Partners, part of BlackRock, viewing it through the lens of opportunity, as BlackRock’s bid for AES could open a new scenario for the firm’s multibillion-dollar lawsuit by bolstering the sued player’s financial standing.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.offshore-energy.biz/33-4-billion-acquisition-of-aes-filling-financial-coffers-for-panamanian-firms-4b-lawsuit/">$33.4 billion acquisition of AES filling financial coffers for Panamanian firms’ $4B lawsuit</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.offshore-energy.biz">Offshore Energy</a>.</p>
]]></description>
		
		
		
		<image>https://www.offshore-energy.biz/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2025/04/LNG_Tankercarousel-Source-US-Department-of-Energy-100x70.jpg?image-crop-positioner-ts=1743577643</image><image_medium>https://www.offshore-energy.biz/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2025/04/LNG_Tankercarousel-Source-US-Department-of-Energy.jpg?image-crop-positioner-ts=1743577643</image_medium><is_in_depth>false</is_in_depth>	</item>
