		<category><![CDATA[Norwegian North Sea]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Odfjell Drilling]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[offshore drilling]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.offshore-energy.biz/?p=792731</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Norway’s state-owned energy giant Equinor has obtained the go-ahead from the Norwegian authorities for drilling activities on the Norwegian Continental Shelf (NCS), which will be undertaken with a semi-submersible rig managed by Odfjell Drilling and owned by Northern Ocean.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.offshore-energy.biz/green-light-for-north-sea-drilling-ops-with-odfjell-drilling-managed-rig/">Green light for North Sea drilling ops with Odfjell Drilling-managed rig</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.offshore-energy.biz">Offshore Energy</a>.</p>
]]></description>
		
		
		
		<image>https://www.offshore-energy.biz/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2025/05/Deepsea-Bollsta-100x70.jpg?image-crop-positioner-ts=1747121839</image><image_medium>https://www.offshore-energy.biz/wp-content/uploads/sites/6/2025/05/Deepsea-Bollsta.jpg?image-crop-positioner-ts=1747121839</image_medium><is_in_depth>false</is_in_depth>	</item>
