		<item>
		<title>Go-ahead for North Sea drilling ops with Odfjell Drilling-managed rig</title>
		<link>https://www.offshore-energy.biz/go-ahead-for-north-sea-drilling-ops-with-odfjell-drilling-managed-rig/</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Melisa Cavcic]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 06 Mar 2026 09:25:14 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[Headline]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Deepsea yantai]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[North Sea]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Norway]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Norwegian North Sea]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Odfjell Drilling]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[offshore drilling]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Wellesley]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Wellesley Petroleum]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.offshore-energy.biz/?p=792697</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Norway’s oil and gas player Wellesley Petroleum has received the blessing from the country’s authorities for the drilling of an exploration well in the Norwegian sector of the North Sea, which is expected to be carried out using a semi-submersible rig managed by Odfjell Drilling, an offshore drilling contractor.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.offshore-energy.biz/go-ahead-for-north-sea-drilling-ops-with-odfjell-drilling-managed-rig/">Go-ahead for North Sea drilling ops with Odfjell Drilling-managed rig</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.offshore-energy.biz">Offshore Energy</a>.</p>
]]></description>
		
		
		
